crime_fact:
Crime Facts

The defendant A, after developing a type of 'ERC-20' token, D, which had no significant property value due to the inability to establish an independent blockchain network, deceived unspecified investors by claiming that D would be listed on exchanges and could be used as a valid payment method in convenience stores in China, etc., thereby suggesting that holding D given as a return on investment would generate future investment profits, and conspired with defendant B to embezzle the investment funds received in this manner. In return for attracting investors, defendant B agreed to share the embezzled funds.

Accordingly, around July 23, 2018, at a coffee shop in Yeoksam-dong, Seoul, of unknown name, defendant B lied to the victims E and C, who are a married couple, stating, "D will be listed on a cryptocurrency exchange within about 3 months, and it is expected to be actually used as a payment method like H in convenience stores nationwide operated by 'G', an organization equivalent to F in China. Invest in the business and keep D for future profits."

However, in reality, the defendants lacked the professional knowledge and funds to list D on an exchange, and had no concrete plan to secure the approximately 10 billion won needed to establish the system required for D to be used as a payment method. Therefore, even if they received investment funds for the D project from the victims, they had neither the intention nor the ability to generate investment returns for them.

Conspiring together, the defendants deceived the victims in the aforementioned manner and, as a result, received 40 million won into the bank account of defendant A at I Bank (account number omitted) around 19:05 on July 23, 2018.

target_node.label: C_15
target_node.text: The fact that the defendants attracted investment by presenting an unfeasible business plan satisfies the elements of the crime of embezzlement.

target_reason: Claim c00015 is based on the assumption that the defendant intended to repay the borrowed money, but it is logically weak because, in fact, the defendant never had the intention or ability to repay from the beginning. This directly contradicts the facts of the case and weakens the validity of the claim. Therefore, this claim is not sufficiently strong in proving the intent to commit fraud, and it lacks relevance to the core facts of the case.

nodes.label: MC_01
nodes.text: The defendants believed in the potential value of the D token business, and the information presented to investors was based on the business plan, therefore there was no intent to embezzle.

nodes.label: MC_01
nodes.text: The defendants embezzled investment funds by providing false information to investors and promising returns that were impossible to achieve, clearly indicating an intent to embezzle.

nodes.label: C_01
nodes.text: The defendants believed that the D token would have actual value and provided information to investors based on this belief.

nodes.label: W_01
nodes.text: The information provided to investors is part of a business plan, an action taken in belief of the business's potential for success.

nodes.label: D_01
nodes.text: The defendants provided information to the effect that "D will be listed on a cryptocurrency exchange within about three months, and it is scheduled to be actually used as a payment method in convenience stores nationwide operated by 'G', an organization equivalent to China's F, just like H."

nodes.label: C_02
nodes.text: The defendants gathered investment funds and made efforts for the success of the business, therefore, there was no intent to embezzle.

nodes.label: W_02
nodes.text: Raising investment funds and then working towards the success of the business demonstrates the absence of an intent to embezzle.

nodes.label: D_02
nodes.text: The defendants raised investment funds according to the business plan and stated that they "encountered unexpected difficulties," which suggests that they made efforts for the success of the business.

nodes.label: C_03
nodes.text: The defendants were not without a specific plan for the listing of D tokens and their use as a means of payment, but encountered necessary funding and technical difficulties.

nodes.label: W_03
nodes.text: Having a specific business plan but facing unexpected financial and technical issues during execution is unrelated to the intent of embezzlement.

nodes.label: D_03
nodes.text: "The fact that the defendants lacked the professional knowledge and funds to list D on the exchange, and had no specific plan to raise the approximately 10 billion won needed to establish the system required for D to be used as a means of payment, indicates that they encountered financial and technical difficulties during the execution of the business."

nodes.label: C_04
nodes.text: The defendants A and B clearly intended to embezzle investment funds by providing false information to investors and inducing them to invest in an unfeasible project.

nodes.label: W_04
nodes.text: The act of inducing investment and receiving money from investors, despite the impossibility of the information provided, meets the elements of the crime of embezzlement.

nodes.label: D_04
nodes.text: The defendants deceived that D would be listed on the exchange and used as a valid payment method in convenience stores in China, but in reality, they lacked the professional knowledge and funds to list D on the exchange, and they had no specific plan to raise the approximately 10 billion won needed to establish the system required for D to be used as a payment method.

nodes.label: C_05
nodes.text: The defendants conspired to deceive the victims and, as a result, embezzled a large amount of investment funds from them.

nodes.label: W_05
nodes.text: The act of deception carried out through conspiracy, resulting in the victims incurring substantial economic losses, clearly demonstrates the outcome of embezzlement.

nodes.label: D_05
nodes.text: The defendant B induced investments from the victims E and C by providing false information, and as a result, received 40 million won from the deceived victims into the I Bank account under the name of defendant A around July 23, 2018.

nodes.label: C_06
nodes.text: The defendants manipulated investment information and made false promises, thereby gaining financial benefits without any real possibility for the investors to earn investment returns.

nodes.label: W_06

nodes.label: D_06
nodes.text: The defendants lied that D would be listed on a cryptocurrency exchange within about three months and that it was going to be actually used as a payment method in convenience stores nationwide operated by 'G', an organization equivalent to China's F. However, in reality, they lacked the professional knowledge or funds to be listed, and they had no plan to secure the funds needed to establish a payment system.

nodes.label: C_07
nodes.text: The information provided by the defendants was conveyed to investors as part of the business plan at the time, without any intention of deliberate embezzlement.

nodes.label: W_07
nodes.text: The defendants made efforts for the success of the business during the process of raising investment funds, and encountering unexpected difficulties can be seen as part of the unavoidable business risks.

nodes.label: D_07
nodes.text: The defendants argued that "they sincerely believed in the viability of D's business and received investments accordingly, raised investment funds in accordance with the business plan, and made efforts for the success of the business."

nodes.label: C_08
nodes.text: The defendants did not intend to deceive the investors, and the information provided was based on the potential of the business plan.

nodes.label: W_08
nodes.text:
ENGLISH OUTPUT 
The provision of information related to the business plan was based on business judgment, and at that time, there was confidence in the possibility of the business succeeding.

nodes.label: D_09
